1. The terminal is a command line tool built into your computer. 

2. GitHub is an open-source website that allows you to store your repositories inside of it. Git is a tool that will enable you to track versions of projects and changes. 

3. The steps to fork a repository are:
	1. Go to the repository you want and click the 'fork' button.
	2. After being taken to the 'create a new fork' page, you will click the 'create fork' button.
	3. Repository has been forked. 
